        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Notes and interpretation\n- All reported stability-constant values here are cumulative logβ for chloride complexes, at 25 °C; enthalpy/entropy entries exist but were excluded from the value ranges above.\n- The cumulative β increases with chloride stoichiometry (β1 < β2 < β3), as expected from stepwise complexation. Reported values span low to high ionic strengths (I up to 4 M), reflecting medium-dependent conditional constants.\n- Media/electrolyte identities are varied in the underlying sources; the summary above focuses on the numeric ranges and ionic strengths available in SRD‑46.",
